ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Participant taking prenatal vitamin in 2nd Trimester
1. Pre-Natal Vitamins
2. Other Multivitamins (e.g. One-A-Day or Centrum)
3. Supplements containing oils or fatty acids (e.g. Omega-3, fish or flaxseed oil)
4. Vitamin D or other single vitamin (e.g. vitamin E or folic acid)
5. Zinc or other mineral (e.g. iron or potassium)
6. Other dietary supplements (e.g. glucosamine chondroitin, coenzyme Q-10, or garlic extract)
7. Amino acid supplements (e.g. lysine)
8. Supplements containing 1 or more herbal or botanical ingredients (e.g. echinacea or St. John's Wort)
9. Fiber supplements (e.g. Metamucil or Fibercon)
10. Over-the-counter antacids (e.g. Tums, Rolaids, or Mylanta)
11. Other supplements
